<section>
<section id="slide-org17a1a68">
<h2 id="org17a1a68">3 case studies</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org17a1a68">
</div></section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-org4fa0999">
<h3 id="org4fa0999">Hinduism &amp; caste system</h3>
<ul>
<li>oldest <b>Vedic</b> hinduism based on the social order of caste system</li>
<li>newer <b>Upanishads</b> focused on individuals, universal Brahman and the release (<b>moksha</b>) from endless cycle of birth &amp; death</li>

</ul>
<ul class="fragment highlight-red">
<li>religion &amp; morality in <b>tension</b> with one another</li>

</ul>
</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-orga4803c5">
<h3 id="orga4803c5">Islam &amp; war (jihad)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Islam born under the burden of persecution &#x2013; Quran approves the use of force when one is wronged</li>
<li>while war not to be undertaken lightly, religious justification for war (cautious)</li>
<li><b>jihad</b> is <b>struggle</b> to expand Islam</li>

</ul>
<ul class="fragment highlight-red">
<li>religion <b>complementing</b> and filling out morality</li>

</ul>
</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-orge29410e">
<h3 id="orge29410e">Christianity &amp; prayer</h3>
<ul>
<li>Pray because we are <b>commanded to</b>?</li>
<li>Pray because it provides <b>good results</b>?</li>
<li>both?</li>

</ul>
<ul class="fragment highlight-red">
<li>religion <b>animating</b> the moral life</li>

</ul>
</section>
</section>
